    <center>
      <h5 class="notkw"><strong>What role does Mathematics play in Art?</strong></h5>
    </center>
  </div>
  <div class="dual-right" style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left;padding-left:1em;border-left: 1px solid #ddd">
      <h5 class="notkw">Topics Include:</h5>
      <ul>
          <li>
              <b>Ideal Proportions</b>
              <ul style="padding-left:1em">
                  <li>What is the <i>ideal</i> human figure?</li>
                  <li>What is the <i>Golden Ratio</i>?</li>
              </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
              <b>Linear Perspective</b>
              <ul style="padding-left:1em">
                  <li>How are visual illusions created with the help of mathematics?</li>
              </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
              <b>Color Theory</b>
              <ul style="padding-left:1em">
                  <li>What are the 3 primary colors?  <i>Why</i> are they the primary colors?
                  </li>
                  <li>
                      My TV say's it's RGB, the printing company says it's CYM, my school
                      teacher says its Red, Blue, and Yellow.  <i><strong>What's going on!?</strong></i>
                  </li>
              </ul>
          </li>
      </ul>
      <ul>
          <li>
              <strong>Math Requirements: </strong>
              <br/>
              High school level mathematics is more than sufficient.
          </li>
          <li>
              <strong>Art Requirements: </strong>
              <br/>
              Simply an openness to see and appreciate art.
          </li>
      </ul>
  </div>
